Head moderately small, 0.38× as wide as elytra (EW/HW=2.62); frontal surface of head capsule slightly convex; punctures on frons fine, with long setae in punctures; eyes small, broadly oval, widest interocular distance 0.53× width of head (
Fig. 4c
). Pronotum 0.61× of elytral width (EW/PW=1.65), pronotal punctures fine, similar to those on head (
Figs 3c, 3f
). Punctures on elytra moderately large, irregular and obviously larger than those on pronotum (
Figs 3a, 3d
).

Surface of prosternum slightly shagreened, punctures moderately large, with sparse short setae (
Figs 3g , 3j
). Mesoventrite slightly shagreened, punctures fine, with several short setae. Metaventrite broad, punctures fine but distinctly larger near discrimen, with short sparse setae ( Figs 3 g–h). Abdominal postcoxal lines complete, almost touching posterior margin of ventrite 1 ( Fig. 4h ).

Female genitalia: Coxites elongate, triangular; styli distinct with terminal setae (
Fig 4n
); spermatheca with a rounded nodulus and a slender, curved cornu (

Fig. 
4m

).
